======================================================================
PART 1: CONE EMBEDDING — Q_m → Q_{m+n}
======================================================================

Cone(T) on n+1 vertices: new vertex n beats everyone.
This adds n new arcs (all pointing away from n), so:
  Q_{m(n)} ↪ Q_{m(n+1)} by adding n fixed arcs.

The embedding is: bits_T → bits_T ⊕ (111...1)_n
(all new arcs set to "new vertex wins" = 1).

Let's trace this embedding for n=4→5.

n=4: m=6, n+1=5: m_cone=10
Extra arcs: 4 = n = 4
  bits=000000: H(T)=1, H(Cone(T))=1, preserved=True
  bits=000001: H(T)=1, H(Cone(T))=1, preserved=True
  bits=000010: H(T)=3, H(Cone(T))=3, preserved=True
  bits=000011: H(T)=1, H(Cone(T))=1, preserved=True
  bits=000100: H(T)=5, H(Cone(T))=5, preserved=True
  bits=000101: H(T)=3, H(Cone(T))=3, preserved=True
  bits=000110: H(T)=5, H(Cone(T))=5, preserved=True
  bits=000111: H(T)=1, H(Cone(T))=1, preserved=True
  bits=001000: H(T)=1, H(Cone(T))=1, preserved=True
  bits=001001: H(T)=3, H(Cone(T))=3, preserved=True

